  "title": "Permanent Senior Embedded Software Engineer at Ang Mo Kio, Up to $8,500 (Office hours)",
  "description": "<p><strong>- Permanent</strong></p><p><strong>- Up to $8,500</strong></p><p><strong>- Mon–Fri, 8:30am–5:30pm</strong></p><p><strong>- Ang Mo Kio</strong><br /></p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Collaborate with other engineering teams and system architects to obtain product features from analysis to deployment phases.</li><li>Implement the design in C and unit test all the software components.</li><li>Verify and validate software system on target hardware.</li><li>Perform the necessary software maintenance and give consultancy to users on the deployed software.</li><li>Continuously develop new skills & techniques in software technologies to improve and reduce software development time and effort.</li><li>Participate in the definition of the future products.</li><li>Enhance infrastructures to hit performance and reliability metrics.</li><li>Drive data-driven decisions through metrics, experimentation, and experience.</li><li>Own problems end-to-end, thinking through everything from user experience, data models, scalability, operability, and ongoing metrics.</li><li>Mentor teammates and contribute to the growth of individuals and the overall team.</li><li>Craft our long-term technical vision with high standards and align with business directions.</li><li>Influence the organization culture by challenging the status quo, think different and being ever curious.</li></ul><p></p><p><br /><strong>Period:</strong></p><ul><li>Permanent </li></ul><p><br /><strong>Working Hours:</strong></p><ul><li>Mon–Fri, 8:30am–5:30pm​  </li></ul><p><br /><strong>Salary: </strong></p><ul><li>Up to $8,500</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Location: </strong></p><ul><li>Ang Mo Kio</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Knowledge in Electrical or Computer Engineering or equivalent</li><li>More than 5 years of experience in embedded system software development, RTOS and/or Linux.</li><li>Good understanding of low-level device drivers like CAN, UART or SPI.</li><li>Solid programming skill in C/C++.</li><li>Good understanding of unit testing.</li><li>Demonstrate a hunger for new knowledge and the ability to quickly source, test and demo ideas.</li><li>Excellent communicator and able to thrive in a fluid, flexible and innovative environment</li><li>Experience in agile software development and embedded system product development from power-on to full functional system.</li><li>Understands hardware, able to read schematics and data sheets.</li><li>Must be interested in space / satellites / remote imagining.</li><li>Singaporean only.</li></ul><p></p><p>Interested applicants, kindly email your detailed resume (<strong>MS Word</strong> format is preferred):<br /><strong>zikry@successhrc.com.sg</strong>  (Registration no: <strong>R2198989</strong>)<br /></p><p>Please ensure that applications sent through email are <strong>no bigger than 1Mb</strong>.</p><p>We thank all applicants for your interest but regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates would be notified.<br /></p><p><strong>Success Resource Centre Pte Ltd </strong>(EA License Number: <strong>04C3201</strong>)</p><p>160 Robinson Road, #13-07/08/09 SBF Center, Singapore 06891</p><p>T: 6337 3183 | W: <a href=\"http://www.successhrc.com.sg/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">www.successhrc.com.sg</a> </p><p><br />\n\n</p>",
